column3: This is a database of all constellation lines. It is based on the modern constellations in SkySafari.
For each constellation, a number “from” is assigned to each star touching the lines.
Two “to” columns list the stars defining lines touching the “from” star.
All of the constellation lines can be defined by 1 “from” column and up to 2 “to” columns.
There might be a theorem for this, analogous to the 4 color theorem, but I don't know about it.
The “to” columns are most easily assigned by first going around a closed loop and then following appendages back to the loop.
The constellation index, ordered in an alphabetic sorting of constellation abbreviations.
The number assigned to each star touching lines in a constellation.
The number assigned to each star to end lines in a constellation (2 columns).
